						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup near the Maruḷayyanaguḍi. </p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that at the instance of <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍaḷēśvara</hi> Mallidēvarsa, Mādaseṭṭi Pambagōḍe along with all <hi rend="italic">prabhus</hi> made a grant of 15 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> land to Bomayya.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year Jaya; Āsāḍa, śu. 11, Monday. It is in characters of the 13th century A.D. The cyclic year Jaya occurred twice: (1) Śaka 1156 (1234 A.D.) and (2) Śaka 1216 (1294 A.D.) in that century.</p>						

						</summary>
